# Consuming App Cursor Rule Template

Copy the template below into your consuming app as:
`.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc`

```md
---
description: Design system usage and update contract for this app
alwaysApply: true
---

# Design System Contract

- This app consumes `@handled-ai/design-system` via npm.
- Import components from:
  - `@handled-ai/design-system`
- Current pinned version (update this line in your app):
  - `@handled-ai/design-system: "<PINNED_VERSION>"`
- Pin exact versions only (never `^` or `~`).

# CSS Setup (Critical)

- This app MUST have Tailwind CSS v4 processing at build time.
- The main CSS file (e.g. `src/index.css`) MUST start with:
  ```css
  @import "tailwindcss";
  @import "tw-animate-css";
  ```
- The file MUST contain `:root` CSS variables, `@theme inline` block, and `@layer base` styles.
- Do NOT use pre-compiled Tailwind output as your CSS source file.
- See `CONSUMER_SETUP.md` in the design-system repo for the complete template CSS.
- Vite projects: `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin must be in `vite.config.ts`.
- Non-Vite: `@tailwindcss/postcss` must be in `postcss.config.mjs`.

# Required Peer Dependencies

The design system externalizes these packages -- they MUST be installed in the consuming app:

- `@tanstack/react-table` (DataTable / accounts view)
- `class-variance-authority` (component variants)
- `clsx` + `tailwind-merge` (cn() utility)
- `date-fns` (date formatting)
- `zod` (validation)
- `lucide-react` (icons)
- `radix-ui`, `@radix-ui/react-slot`, `@radix-ui/react-label`

Optional (only if using charts/3D): `recharts`, `@nivo/sankey`, `@nivo/core`, `three`, `@react-three/fiber`, `@react-three/drei`

# Theming Contract

- Do not hard-code colors when a semantic token exists.
- Use semantic tokens such as:
  - `bg-primary`
  - `text-muted-foreground`
  - `border-border`
- Token values are defined by this app's theme variables (`globals.css` or equivalent).

# PrototypeShell Setup

- When building a new app from the prototype, provide ALL inbox callbacks referenced by `detailSections`:
  - `buildSuggestedActions` -- email/action cards
  - `buildSourceItems` -- source context for the detail view
  - `getSignalScore` -- signal score breakdown
  - `getTimelineEvents` -- activity timeline
  - `buildAccountContacts` (preferred) or `accountContacts` -- email To/Cc/Bcc suggestions
  - `emailSignature` -- default signature
- Inbox contact seeding must be account-specific:
  - Every email action should include a recommended contact (`emailMeta.to`)
  - Contact picker suggestions should include additional contacts for that same account
  - Do not use one global mixed-company contact list
  - All seeded contacts MUST have `confirmed: false` so they render in the yellow "requires confirmation" state -- never derive `confirmed` from internal flags like isPowerUser
- Admin/Settings pages MUST use the built-in `views.admin` config (AdminViewConfig) so they render inside the shell with the sidebar visible. Do NOT conditionally replace the entire PrototypeShell with a full-page settings component.
  - Define admin tabs in the config with `id`, `label`, `icon`, and `content` (ReactNode)
  - Add `"admin"` to `navigableViews` and sidebar sections
- The resulting app should look identical to the design system preview at `design.withhandled.app/preview`.

# How to Change Components

- Do not edit package-installed component code in `node_modules`.
- To change shared component behavior:
  1. make the change in the `@handled-ai/design-system` repo
  2. publish a new package version
  3. update this app's pinned dependency version
- Use design-system docs as the API source of truth:
  - `docs/COMPONENTS.md`

# Eject Pattern (Exception Only)

- If this app needs deep one-off customization for a single component:
  - `npx shadcn@latest add @handled/{name}`
- This creates a local copy that diverges from the shared package.
- Once ejected, this app owns ongoing maintenance for that local copy.
- Use this path rarely; prefer upstream changes in the design-system package.
```
